value.value: An individual who specializes in the creation or fitting of orthopedic devices to improve functional capacity.
An individual who specializes in the fitting of breast prosthetics.
An individual who specializes in the fitting of pedorthic devices.
An individual who has training/certification in the application of exercise in the treatment of disease.
A semiquantitative finding indicating that the concentration of CA19-9 detected in a sample is greater than 500 U/mL.

A rare, benign cystic neoplasm that arises from the apocrine gland. It is characterized by the presence of papillary-like epithelial projections and more complex architectural patterns compared to apocrine hidrocystoma.
A morphologic finding indicating the presence of papillary projections lined by epithelial cells in a tumor sample.
A regimen consisting of gemcitabine and bevacizumab that may be used in the treatment of ovarian, fallopian tube, and primary peritoneal cancer.
A poroma with eccrine differentiation.
A poroma with apocrine differentiation.
A response from an individual, on a form or verbally, that they are female.
A response from an individual, on a form or verbally, that they are male.

A person's innate sense of their self as female. This identity may be at odds with their sex assigned at birth. Gender identity is different from gender expression, how they display their self outwardly.

A person's innate sense of their self as male. This identity may be at odds with their sex assigned at birth. Gender identity is different from gender expression, how they display their self outwardly.
A person's innate sense of their self as neither female nor male.
Having no gender.

Fibroblast growth factor 2 (288 aa, ~31 kDa) is encoded by the human FGF2 gene. This protein plays a role in the regulation of cell proliferation, angiogenesis, and limb and nervous system development.
Having a gender that fluctuates or changes between male, female, other, and/or none.
Having a gender that differs from a sex assigned at birth.
The male or female designation that doctors ascribe to a newborn infant, usually based on the appearance of the child's external genitalia, and that is marked on their birth records.
Refers to an individual that was identified as male as a newborn infant, based on their external genitalia or other physical characteristics, with this designation noted on their birth records.
Refers to an individual that was identified as female as a newborn infant, based on their external genitalia or other physical characteristics, with this designation noted on their birth records.
A poroma characterized by the presence of aggregates of basaloid cells confined to the epidermis.
A poroma characterized by the presence of a single or several nodules of neoplastic cells forming solid and cystic areas in the dermis.
A category of terminology used to qualify the information pertaining to substances in the framework of the Pharmaceutical Quality/Chemistry, Manufacturing and Controls documents.
The amount of micrograms of a substance contained in a single actuation of a device.
A unit of presentation to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of bait.
Fibroblast growth factor 1 (17 aa, ~155 kDa) is encoded by the human FGF1 gene. This protein plays a role in cell proliferation, angiogenesis, cell differentiation, and cell migration.
Solid, single dose preparation for veterinary use consisting of a suspension intended for oral use, encased in a solid outer mass that is attractive to the target species.

A type of solid pharmaceutical dose form consisting of a mass that contains products that are attractive to the target species; active substance(s) may be incorporated into the mass itself, or may be enclosed inside the mass, usually inside an internal protective container such as a blister.
Denotes the inhabitants of Somalia, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.
An individual or their descendants with origins in Ghana.
A regimen consisting of prednisone and sirolimus that may be used in the treatment of certain histiocytic neoplasms, such as Erdheim-Chester disease (ECD).
Denotes a person from El Salvador.
Denotes a person from Guatemala.
Denotes a person from Honduras.
Denotes a person from Colombia.
Denotes a person from Morocco.
Fibroblast growth factor 3 (239 aa, ~27 kDa) is encoded by the human FGF3 gene. This protein is involved in embryonic development, cell proliferation, and cell differentiation.
Denotes a person from Yemen.
Denotes a member of the Kurdish people.

label.value: MYC Gene Rearrangement and BCL2 Gene Rearrangement Positive

value.value: An indication that both rearrangements involving the MYC gene and rearrangements involving the BCL2 gene were detected in the same sample.
Individuals from the Congo Basin, Republic of the Congo and the Democratic Republic of the Congo.

label.value: MYC Gene Rearrangement and BCL6 Gene Rearrangement Positive

value.value: An indication that both rearrangements involving the MYC gene and rearrangements involving the BCL6 gene were detected in the same sample.

A fusion gene that results from a chromosomal rearrangment involving the long arm of chromosome 11 (11q) which fuses exon 1, 5 or 6 of the YAP1 gene to exon 2 of the MAML2 gene. This rearrangement may be associated with various neoplastic diseases including but not restricted to: nasopharyngeal carcinoma, NF2-wild type meningioma/schwannoma, ovarian carcinoma, poroma/porocarcinoma, metaplasic thymoma, and both retiform and composite hemangioendothelioma.

A fusion gene that results from a chromosomal translocation which fuses exon 2, 3, 4, 6 or 8 of the YAP1 gene on chromosome 11 to exon 2 or 3 of the NUTM1 gene on chromosome 15. This rearrangement may be associated with poroma/porocarcinoma.

label.value: MYC Gene Rearrangement, BCL2 Gene Rearrangement, and BCL6 Gene Rearrangement Positive

value.value: An indication that all three rearrangements involving the MYC gene, BCL2 gene, and BCL6 gene were detected in the same sample.
A regimen consisting of bortezomib, dexamethasone, isatuximab and lenalidomide that may be used for the treatment of multiple myeloma.
A person whose occupation is to fit physical objects to individuals to improve function.
